HEADWORD: Dumple
<hw>Dum"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Dumpling</er>.]</ety> <def>To make dumpy; to fold, or bend, as one
part over another.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was a little man, <qex>dumpled</qex> up together.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dumpling</ent>⟦br⟧
